課程概述 Course Description
       何瑞文: 1. Catalyst and Catalysis  2. The Applied Catalysts: a. Ethanolic acid, b. Flavorings-aspartame, c. Polymers-PE, d. Fertilizers-ammonia 翁鴻山: 1. Catalyst Preparation and Manufacture 2. Supported Metal Catalysts 3. Acid and Zeolite Catalysts 4. Nano, Mesoporous and Monolithic Catalysts 5. Laboratory Reactors and Experimental Methods 6. Catalysts for Cleaner Production Processes and Environmental Protection 7. Catalysts for Energy-related Technologies (Including photo-catalysts and catalysts for fuel cells) 何瑞文: 1. Characterization of Catalytic Materials: Gas Adsorption, Vibration Spectroscopy, X-ray Spectroscopy, Electron Spectroscopy, Ion Spectroscopy 2. Applications: CO oxidation, Nano Carbon Materials, Hydrogen Production, etc. 3. New Finding in Catalysis何瑞文: 1. Catalyst and Catalysis  2. The Applied Catalysts: a. Ethanolic acid, b. Flavorings-aspartame, c. Polymers-PE, d. Fertilizers-ammonia 翁鴻山: 1. Catalyst Preparation and Manufacture 2. Supported Metal Catalysts 3. Acid and Zeolite Catalysts 4. Nano, Mesoporous and Monolithic Catalysts 5. Laboratory Reactors and Experimental Methods 6. Catalysts for Cleaner Production Processes and Environmental Protection 7. Catalysts for Energy-related Technologies (Including photo-catalysts and catalysts for fuel cells) 何瑞文: 1. Characterization of Catalytic Materials: Gas Adsorption, Vibration Spectroscopy, X-ray Spectroscopy, Electron Spectroscopy, Ion Spectroscopy 2. Applications: CO oxidation, Nano Carbon Materials, Hydrogen Production, etc. 3. New Finding in Catalysis    

